cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.DS, cs.SE 

This paper is about automated machine learning, which involves designing methods that can automatically perform model selection and hyperparameter optimization without human intervention. This topic is closely related to several sub-categories of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and software engineering (cs.SE). Given the focus on machine learning and optimization, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories. However, the use of neural networks and computer vision datasets suggests that cs.CV is also a strong possibility. Finally, the emphasis on meta-learning and Bayesian regression could also make cs.DS and cs.SE relevant sub-categories.
